tool_description: The API behind Stamp's mobile app.
name: Stamp
title: Stamp

api_list.name: Get passport list
api_list.description: Get a list of the logged in user's passports and their respective recommendations.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://frank611-stamp-v1.p.rapidapi.com/passport"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "frank611-stamp-v1.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

api_list.name: Redirect to a user's profile picture
api_list.description: Redirects (301) to a user's profile picture. This does not return a json object.

api_list.name: Get a request
api_list.description: Gets the request with the specified ID. Note that this allows to get any request by any user. Requests are therefore considered "public". Also note that this only returns the json info for the request. To get to the request's web page, go to 'http://xxxx/request/:id' (without the /api)
